content:
After your Einstein Reply Recommendations model is activated, you can pause recommendations if you need to. You can also update, delete, and customize access to your published replies so they continue to meet your needs.

You don't need to pause recommendations to publish replies or manage published replies. See Review and Publish Replies.

After the initial build, you can check for new reply templates on-demand by selecting the Reply Candidates tab and then Check for New Replies.

Duplicate replies can occur if a reply was published multiple times or highly similar replies werenâ€™t edited or removed during publishing.

To address duplicate replies, delete or edit the duplicates from the Quick Text tab. If you save your replies in multiple quick text folders, verify that agents don't have access to both folders.

Pause Reply Recommendations by clicking Pause Recommendations on the Einstein Reply Recommendations Setup page.

If you disable the feature rather than pausing it, reply recommendations stop and the Einstein Replies component disappear from page layouts. Published replies are still available as quick text records.
title: Maintaining Recommended Replies in Service Cloud
